PSPDFKit runs on Android devices with:

- Android <%= guide_constant('android', 'min_sdk_version_name') %> or newer / API level <%= guide_constant('android', 'min_sdk_version') %> or higher.
- 32-bit or 64-bit ARM (armeabi-v7a with NEON / arm64-v8a) or 32-bit or 64-bit Intel x86 CPU.

For development, you will need:

- Android Studio <%= guide_constant('android', 'recommended_android_studio_version') %> or newer (or any other editor/IDE/build chain that supports Gradle).
- To set your `targetSdkVersion` to <%= guide_constant('android', 'target_sdk_version') %>.
- We recommend building your Android apps using Android Gradle plugin <%= guide_constant('android', 'android_gradle_plugin_version') %> or higher.

We reevaluate the minimum Android version from time to time based on [Google’s device statistics][]. As of September 2018, with supporting Android 4.4, you cover more than 96.4 percent of all devices on the market. See [Mixpanel Android OS versions][] and the [Android version distribution history][] for more information.

## AndroidX Support

Starting with [version 5.1][] of PSPDFKit for Android, we are using [AndroidX][] instead of the support library. This means that your app also needs to be updated to use AndroidX. You can check out our migration guide [here][migration].

